Class DecisionTree

public class DecisionTree
extends CwObject

DecisionTree Decision Tree presents graphically complex logic and reduces overall maintenance effort by dividing it in smaller pieces. The Decision Trees look like and work like processes and run synchronously as uninterrupted units in a single session (server thread). They resemble the single task process flows that were implemented in AVM version 4.1. However single task process flows were able to execute (with certain limitations) only within a Process engine, while Decision Trees can run in any AVM environment. As AVM version 5 does not any more support process flows, single tasks process flows are not supported too. Functionally they are replaced by Decision Trees in AVM version 5.1.
